{
  "texts": [
    "IKS at |ν| = 2From the degenerate manifold of |ν| = 2 IKS states, we can pick the spin singlet state, where the same 'primitive' IKS state is occupied in both spin sectors.",
    "The arguments for the Goldstone mode counting turn out to be very similar to KIVC state at ν = 0, namely, the broken generators are τ z and s x,y,z τ z.",
    "It can again be shown that ρ vanishes identically, leading to 4 linearly dispersing Goldstone modes.",
    "IKS at |ν| = 3The IKS state at |ν| = 3 has finite spin polarization in each valley.",
    "Since an SU (2) ferromagnet has one quadratic Goldstone mode, we expect |ν| = 3 to have two quadratic Goldstone modes from the spin polarization of each valley."
  ]
}